<div><h3>SPAN 246 - Studies in Spanish Cinema </h3>  <p><hr>&#8220;Film and Society in Contemporary Spain&#8221;</p>

<p>Surveys principal Spanish films and filmmakers of the past 25 years in the context of political and social change in Spain. Considers formulation of cultural ideologies and identities through topics such as Immigration, LGTBQ, New Technologies and &#8220;Nacionalismos&#8221;. Topics vary each time the course is offered. Conducted in Spanish.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=29&coid=98537" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=98537&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=98537&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt1182" target="_blank">SPAN 133</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span>Â OR PERM; NATIVE SPEAKERS WELCOME<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> LP, DI<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered periodically<br><br><strong>Placement Guidelines</strong><br> Please visit the <a href="http://www.clarku.edu/departments/foreign/undergraduate/placement.cfm" target="_blank">Department of Language, Literature and Culture </a>for the language placement guidelines.<br><br></p><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt1182"></div></div>		</td>
